07040nam a22009735i 9783110679830DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2019956256  a97831106798307 a10.1515/97831106798302doi  a(DE-B1597)537208  a(OCoLC)1153458195  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aART0000002bisacsh00aUselessness :bHumankind’s most valuable tool? /ced. by Michelle Howard, Luciano Parodi. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (152 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tCONTRIBUTORS -- tPREFACE. USELESSNESS IS A RAREFIED THING -- tINFREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS: Excavating Obsolete Migrant Skills -- tREFUSING TO PERFORM: Trans-Utility, or the contemporary value of uselessness in architecture -- tUSELESSNESS AND PURPOSELESSNESS: On central norms and imperatives of Western aesthetics -- tUSELESS, AND THEN DANGEROUS: Public Space and Property in 20th century British Modernist Housing -- tUSELESS ARCHITECTURE -- tUSE–LESS–LAND: Two centuries of defending Tempelhofer Field in Berlin -- tIN THE BEGINNING THERE WAS USELESSNESS -- tCONQUEST OF THE USELESS -- tART—USE— USEFULNESS. Two Discourses: Use Value and Instrumentalization -- tEPILOGUE: USELESSNESS, XXXXXi0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIs uselessness a tool? The acquisition of tools is the secret to humankind’s success and what distinguishes us from animals. However, we also use tools to tell stories and produce objects that are perplexingly useless. Uselessness rarely meets our expectations, but can also be fascinating and liberating, because it eludes the logic of the "use = value" equation. In the Modern Age usefulness became a priority: with reference to space, production or training. Yet futurologists today predict that one product of artificial intelligence will be a "useless" future. If the future makes us useless, it will be necessary to reconsider our attitude toward uselessness. The texts in this interdisciplinary reader illuminate the potential creativity the future can bring in light of this development.  aIst Nutzlosigkeit ein Werkzeug? Die Errungenschaft von Werkzeugen ist das Erfolgsgeheimnis der Menschheit und macht den Unterschied zur Tierwelt. Doch wir nutzen Werkzeuge auch, um Geschichten zu erzählen und Objekte herzustellen, deren Nutzlosigkeit verwirrt. Nutzlosigkeit entspricht selten unseren Erwartungen, kann aber auch faszinieren und befreien, weil sie sich der Logik „Gebrauch = Wert“ entzieht. Mit der Moderne wurde Nützlichkeit zur Priorität: in Bezug auf Raum, Produktion oder Bildung. Doch mittlerweile sagen Zukunftsforscher voraus, dass mit der Artificial Intelligence eine „nutzlose“ Gesellschaft entsteht. Wenn die Zukunft uns nutzlos macht, gilt es, unsere Haltung zur Nutzlosigkeit zu überdenken. Die Texte des Readers beleuchten, was uns die Zukunft in diesem Sinne an Kreativität einbringen könnte.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aFuture Science. 4aSociety. 4aUseless. 7aART / General.2bisacsh1 aDiederichsen, Diedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatherley, Owen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Michelle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKurbak, Ebru, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeimer, Sonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParedes Maldonado, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo